It constantly puzzles me what categories and language people (read: normies) use. Like is "babied" here meant to represent being hugged, seeping together with the mother, or like "baby talk", etc.? It's like 17th century medics equating alcohol and shellfish as "hot" substances.

No hate to Mr. OP, but there are so many of these concepts, words that combine a hundred contradictory things inside themselves and people continuously treat them as a group even if it is completely arbitrary. We are so careless with words and meanings, we produce "idle chatter".

One of the things that horrified Dr. Ray Peat the most in his emails was when someone told him they had been "peating", because it sometimes meant eating two loaves of bread daily or taking 15 pharmaceuticals w/ soda. The sea-sickening imprecision of words with changing meanings.
